# Project Architecture Rules

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This project follows a **Hybrid Architecture** (Firebase Hosting + Cloud Run).
> Detailed rules and deployment instructions are maintained in: [DEVELOPMENT_GUIDE.md](file:///Users/wayne/FiveNursings/RESOURCES/DEVELOPMENT_GUIDE.md#L105-L131)

## Core Deployment
- **Backend (API)**: `gcloud run deploy api --source . --project fivenursings-73917017-a0dfd`
- **Frontend**: `firebase deploy --only hosting`

## Safety Guidelines
- **DO NOT** migrate backend logic from Cloud Run back to Firebase Functions.
- Ensure `gcloud` points to **Project B (fivenursings-73917017-a0dfd)**.
- For all API paths, ensure they match the Hosting rewrites (`/api/**`).
- **User ID Standard**: ALWAYS use `resolveUserIds` on the backend for logic involving `userId` (symptoms, logs, tasks). NEVER assume a single ID format (Firebase UID vs MongoDB ID).
- **Database Isolation**: NEVER hardcode `fivenursing_pro`. Use `process.env.NODE_ENV` or `MONGODB_DB_NAME` to determine the database name dynamically. Default to `fivenursing_dev` in development.
